<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-05-19T08:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-05-19T08:35:00-05:00" n="454" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d454">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">701.9111/557: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Merriam</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-19T17:00:00+03:25">May 19, 1936—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 19—1:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>35. Department’s telegram 25, May 18, 6 p.m. Saw Foreign Minister this
                            afternoon. He was hesitant about stating Iranian position in writing but
                            agreed to consider the request and to inform me of decision.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Merriam</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>